Course Objectives
 To provide an understanding of the global environmental context, sustainable  development, and the legal, institutional, and procedural frameworks of Environmental Impact Assessment (EIA) in India and worldwide.
 To develop knowledge of EIA processes and methods, including screening, scoping, impact identification, costbenefit analysis, and cumulative and socio-economic impact  assessments.
 To enable students to design and evaluate Environmental Management Plans (EMPs), mitigation and rehabilitation strategies, and conduct environmental audits and postproject evaluations through case studies of infrastructure and industrial projects.
 To build competence in applying Life Cycle Assessment (LCA) for evaluating  environmental systems, sustainability performance, and decision-making, in line with ISO 14040 guidelines.
 To introduce students to risk assessment approaches, toxicology principles, and sustainability assessment methodologies, including sustainability indicators, metrics, and reporting frameworks.

Prerequisite: Nil

For IoT students - the course will be handled by Dr. Angel Jessieleena A
For AI-DS students - the course will be handled by Dr. Uthra Devi K

COURSE OBJECTIVES
 To understand basic concepts and terminologies of quantum computing.
 To compose programs in Qiskit.
 To construct programs using quantum algorithms.

1. QUANTUM STATES AND QUBITS: 9
Introduction, The Atoms of Computation, Representing Qubit States, Single Qubit Gates
2. MULTIPLE QUBITS AND ENTANGLEMENT: 9
Multiple Qubits and Entangled States, More Circuit Identities, Qiskit, quantum computing and Python
3. QUANTUM PROTOCOLS AND QUANTUM ALGORITHMS: 9
Defining Quantum Circuits, Deutsch-Jozsa Algorithm, Bernstein-Vazirani Algorithm, Quantum Fourier Transform, Quantum Phase Estimation, Shor's Algorithm
4. QUANTUM ALGORITHMS FOR APPLICATIONS: 9
Applied Quantum Algorithms, Solving Linear Systems of Equations using HHL, Simulating Molecules using VQE, Grover's Algorithm
5. QUANTUM MACHINE LEARNING: 9
Hybrid quantum-classical Neural Networks with PyTorch and Qiskit, , Quantum Teleportation, Superdense Coding, Quantum Key Distribution Quantum support vector machines, Quantum Neural Networks

TOTAL PERIODS: 45

COURSE OUTCOMES:
After the completion of this course, students will be able to:
 Understand and develop introductory concepts of quantum computing
 Represent compound data using quantum protocols and algorithms
 Perform basic quantum machine learning computations.

TEXT BOOK:

1. Qiskit Textbook:
https://qiskit.org/textbook/preface.html
2. YouTube Quantum learning series: https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PLOFEBzvs-Vvp2xg9-POLJhQwtVktlYGbY
3. Quantum Computation and Quantum Information, Textbook by M. A. Nielsen and I. Chuang, Cambridge University Press (2010)
